item.title: Models go through character?
item.dc:creator: @iBunnie iBunnie
item.description:
@iBunnie wrote:

[quote=“nardoscape, post:26, topic:472602”][quote author=iBunnie link=topic=590404.msg4179689#msg4179689 date=1355365506]

I already added, the cape in item.cfg before I posted this. It is also in itemdef.java client side. I honestly have no idea what the problem is

Uh, go to itemassistant.java and find:

	public String itemType(int item) {

and make a thing for the cape like this:

		if (item == ****) {
			return "cape";
		}

-Make sure you change the **** to your items ID.

Well the good news is that the cape is now in the cape slot, but the bad news is, it still appears through my character (as shown in the pciture above)

Replace your model.java with mine:
http://pastebin.com/Bvp9bqjG

Tell me if it works.
[/quote]

Works! Appreciate the help homie! <333[/quote]
Yeah no problem, i had the same problem a while back and ended up having to rewrite my model header. Also, i made my model header for 602 character files, you may want to add those. (They look better anyways)

Read full topic
